<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> unless she waits 9 months and camps it which she cant do or she goes with the guild when he pops and kills it the way Verant intended. If she asks I will go for her and kill it and I dont give a rats ass about the list or you Delores thanks. Sad fact is though Sumer wont ever ask because though she wants it shes too nice to jump the list even though she cant camp it.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
So we have a cleric that's played for three years, who can't spare the time to camp the epic but can gather the force necessary to grab a pop from whoever is there. This cleric refuses to do so, though, because they actually feel some compassion for the other clerics that ARE camping it.<br>
<br>
I started playing Xmas 1999. Between work and associated activities (travel, getting ready for work in the morning etc.) I spend 12 hours per day working. There's no way I could camp Ragefire, especially given that I refuse to share account info. I'm in a guild that could take the pop if it ever wanted it, Lotus Cult. I'm about as firm a supporter of the list as you'll find. I've had my pearl for the heart container for months - it is my last step.<br>
<br>
Sumer isn't the only cleric in this boat. It sucks. But spreading the misery around is not the answer. Having a list lessens the drama, and allows guilds to schedule raids and what not around the time they expect their cleric to be due to help camp. It lets more people be away from the zone and off doing more useful things than stare at a patch of ground and hope their KS team can outdamage the other clerics' KS teams.<br>
<br>
On the bright side, it sounds like there's another change to the quest coming soon. Apparently having the situation be mentioned in a BBC news piece rattled a few cages at VI. I have no idea how miserable the new quest will be, or how many steps clerics that are currently at Ragefire will need to complete afterwards, but I sincerely hope it changes things for the better - for Sumer, for me, and for all the clerics on the list right now.<br>
